WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:03.302
Sal: Attention staff,
<i>the annual childrens hospital</i>

00:03.304 --> 00:06.305
<i>Fundraiser gala will start</i>
<i>tonight at 6:00 p.M. Sharp.</i>

00:06.307 --> 00:07.873
<i>The host</i>
<i>of this year's fundraiser</i>

00:07.875 --> 00:10.676
<i>Will be the one and only</i>
<i>suspense thriller novelist</i>

00:10.678 --> 00:11.910
<i>Dean koontz.</i>
[ gasps ]

00:11.912 --> 00:12.845
Dean koontz!
What?!

00:12.847 --> 00:13.879
I have all his books.

00:13.881 --> 00:14.980
<i>And...</i>
Hey!

00:14.982 --> 00:16.949
He said, "and."

00:16.951 --> 00:18.150
<i>...That is all.</i>

00:18.152 --> 00:19.985
Oh, there it is.

00:19.987 --> 00:23.322
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

00:27.327 --> 00:31.764
We'll see you on the other side,
old friend.

00:31.766 --> 00:35.234
No, I am not nervous
because

00:35.236 --> 00:37.169
The rich benefactors
are gonna see dean koontz,

00:37.171 --> 00:38.971
And they're just gonna write
those checks.

00:38.973 --> 00:40.472
Oh, yeah.

00:40.474 --> 00:42.541
And all we got to do is take
those checks to the bank,

00:42.543 --> 00:43.642
Fill out a deposit form,

00:43.644 --> 00:45.611
Wait in line
for the next available teller,

00:45.613 --> 00:46.779
Give her the checks,

00:46.781 --> 00:49.581
Show her a form
of government-issue I.D.,

00:49.583 --> 00:50.749
And then the next day...

00:50.751 --> 00:52.651
Wait in line
for the next available teller,

00:52.653 --> 00:54.753
Give her the checks,
assuming that it is a woman,

00:54.755 --> 00:57.222
Show her a form
of government-issue I.D.,

00:57.224 --> 00:58.490
And then the next day...

00:58.492 --> 01:00.692
If the deposit is made
by 6:00 p.M.,

01:00.694 --> 01:03.729
Second business day
if after that, we get the money.

01:03.731 --> 01:06.031
Literally <i> exactly</i>
how it will happen.

01:06.033 --> 01:08.233
Sy, what's dean koontz's
phone number?

01:08.235 --> 01:11.070
I want to call him to arrange
his travel from the airport.

01:11.072 --> 01:13.038
<i>You</i> are gonna call
dean koontz?

01:13.040 --> 01:14.206
Mm-hmm.
A <i> nurse?</i>

01:14.208 --> 01:16.341
That is so funny
I forgot to laugh.

01:16.343 --> 01:19.078
I literally can't remember
how to do

01:19.080 --> 01:21.280
What is normally
an automatic reflex.

01:22.715 --> 01:25.150
<i>I</i> will call koontz,
not a nurse.

01:25.152 --> 01:26.819
Good luck with that,
sy.

01:26.821 --> 01:28.320
But you know what?

01:28.322 --> 01:29.488
Don't tell koontz that there's
an anonymous blogger

01:29.490 --> 01:30.756
Who writes scathing reviews

01:30.758 --> 01:32.191
Of childrens hospital
staying here.

01:32.193 --> 01:34.126
Dean: Hi, you've reached
dean koontz...

01:34.128 --> 01:36.395
An anonymous blogger.
What blog?

01:36.397 --> 01:39.498
Thelongtermcarewing.Com.
Everybody reads it.

01:39.500 --> 01:43.202
But it's just some kid
who writes scathing reviews

01:43.204 --> 01:44.703
Of the hospitals
he's staying in

01:44.705 --> 01:46.605
Because he's bitter
about dying young.

01:46.607 --> 01:48.540
But lola,
if we get a bad review,

01:48.542 --> 01:50.476
No one is gonna write us
a check.

01:50.478 --> 01:52.277
[ sighs ] and if we don't
get the checks,

01:52.279 --> 01:53.579
Then we can't
drive to the bank

01:53.581 --> 01:55.180
And fill out
a deposit form and --

01:55.182 --> 01:56.882
Thelongtermcarewing.Com,
huh?

01:56.884 --> 01:58.283
Yeah.

01:58.285 --> 02:01.687
Oh, I think I know
where to find this dying kid.

02:06.526 --> 02:09.026
Nurse beth,
everything has to be perfect.

02:09.029 --> 02:11.096
No! This goes there,
that goes there.

02:11.098 --> 02:12.531
Are you
the hospital administrator?

02:12.533 --> 02:14.333
What,
are you writing a book?
Well...

02:14.335 --> 02:15.601
Why don't you leave
the questions

02:15.603 --> 02:17.069
To those people
who do write books,

02:17.071 --> 02:19.938
Like supernatural mystery writer
dean koontz.

02:19.940 --> 02:21.106
Besides, I'm busy.

02:21.108 --> 02:22.407
I do write a blog.

02:25.745 --> 02:26.845
Hi.

02:26.847 --> 02:28.046
Sy middleman.

02:28.048 --> 02:30.082
I am
the head administrator.

02:30.084 --> 02:31.483
What can I do
to make your stay

02:31.485 --> 02:33.218
Right here in this hospital
better?

02:33.220 --> 02:34.920
I need a bed
closer to an outlet.

02:34.922 --> 02:36.288
A lot of people
read my blog,

02:36.290 --> 02:38.123
And I need to
keep my devices juiced.

02:38.125 --> 02:39.391
You stay right there.

02:39.393 --> 02:41.793
All right, young man,
come with me.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.128
I'm dizzy.

02:43.130 --> 02:46.765
We're just doing
a little regular relocating.

02:46.767 --> 02:47.866
No, no, no, no, no.

02:47.868 --> 02:49.434
Let's get you
out of this stuffy room

02:49.436 --> 02:51.036
While nurse beth cleans up
this kid's filth.

02:51.038 --> 02:53.805
And zoom, zoom,
zoom, zoom, zoom.

02:53.807 --> 02:54.907
I still feel dizzy.

02:54.909 --> 02:56.375
I'm gonna take terry
on a tour.

02:56.377 --> 02:58.177
Huh?
I'm taking terry
on a tour.

02:58.179 --> 03:01.680
Huh?
I'm taking terry
on a tour.

03:02.815 --> 03:03.815
Huh?

03:03.817 --> 03:04.816
Terry on a tour!

03:04.818 --> 03:05.951
Terry on a tour.

03:05.953 --> 03:07.486
Here we go.
Terry on a tour.

03:07.488 --> 03:09.188
We're touring, terry.

03:10.423 --> 03:11.823
Huh?

03:13.960 --> 03:16.828
And this is my favorite
second-floor hallway.

03:16.830 --> 03:18.330
It's the linen closet.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.699
I want to tell you something --
state of the art.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.501
Is that the cafeteria?
I'm starved.

03:22.503 --> 03:24.136
Yeah, you don't want to eat
that garbage.

03:24.138 --> 03:27.272
I mean, the food is great.
It's the garbage that's awful.

03:27.274 --> 03:28.640
Actually,
I changed my mind.

03:28.642 --> 03:30.175
I'm gonna go back to my room
and write that review

03:30.177 --> 03:31.810
Before the fundraiser
tonight.

03:31.812 --> 03:35.147
No, you don't want to write
a review <i> before</i> dinner,

03:35.149 --> 03:37.015
Because,
as a special surprise,

03:37.017 --> 03:40.919
Our chef phillipe is making us
a private meal.

03:40.921 --> 03:45.023
Oh, and he is <i> french.</i>

03:45.025 --> 03:46.391
Whoa!

03:46.393 --> 03:47.826
Did you just say
that your chef was french?

03:47.828 --> 03:48.927
What are you, a cop?

03:48.929 --> 03:50.495
Why don't you leave
the interrogations

03:50.497 --> 03:52.130
To guys
like detective john calvino,

03:52.132 --> 03:54.933
The harried cop in dean koontz's
number-one bestseller

03:54.935 --> 03:56.134
"what the night knows."

03:56.136 --> 03:57.636
Well, I do write
a very popular blog

03:57.638 --> 03:59.871
Called
thelongtermcarewing.Com.

04:00.807 --> 04:01.773
What did you just say?

04:01.775 --> 04:03.609
I thought
you were the blogger.

04:03.611 --> 04:06.245
Yeah, hundreds of middle-age men
flock to my site every week

04:06.247 --> 04:07.980
To see videos
of cheerleaders falling down.

04:07.982 --> 04:09.815
So, it's settled then.
Dinner for three?

04:09.817 --> 04:11.416
Yeah. It was on the tip
of my tongue.

04:11.418 --> 04:12.718
Dinner for three.

04:12.720 --> 04:13.919
Excuse me.

04:17.457 --> 04:19.992
[ muffled scream ]

04:25.498 --> 04:27.432
Oh, getting
some foot stomping in

04:27.434 --> 04:29.268
Before the big night,
huh, sy?

04:29.270 --> 04:30.302
That's your thing.

04:30.304 --> 04:32.271
You don't know me.

04:35.308 --> 04:36.675
[ scoffs ]

04:36.677 --> 04:38.910
Ooh, I'm wearing a tux
to the fundraiser

04:38.912 --> 04:42.414
Because I believe
in gender-neutral formal wear

04:42.416 --> 04:45.117
And also because my body is
a terrifying mess.

04:45.119 --> 04:46.518
I'm not even gonna go.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.120
I'm probably just gonna hang out
and do my thing.

04:48.122 --> 04:50.355
What's this "thing" kick
you're on?

04:50.357 --> 04:52.758
Everybody's got a thing,
like your thing is

04:52.760 --> 04:55.827
Drinking from a bottle
of extra-strength laxative 24/7.

04:55.829 --> 04:59.197
What's your thing?
My thing is pointing out
other people's things.

04:59.199 --> 05:02.367
And that thing, it's like --
it's like the king of things.

05:02.369 --> 05:05.070
Well, I'll do my thing.

05:05.072 --> 05:07.506
You do your thing.

05:09.809 --> 05:10.842
Ahh!

05:10.844 --> 05:12.177
Sal: Attention staff,

05:12.179 --> 05:13.745
<i>Bob odenkirk played a lawyer</i>
<i>on "breaking bad."</i>

05:13.747 --> 05:16.381
<i>That is saul.</i>
[is all]

05:19.819 --> 05:21.653
[ clatters ]

05:34.667 --> 05:36.435
[ clatters ]
oh!

05:36.437 --> 05:38.003
Nurse beth, no questions.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.404
You're gonna be my waiter.

05:39.406 --> 05:41.640
All right.
Let's go over mise-en-place.

05:41.642 --> 05:44.443
Now, in order to emulate
the french style of cooking,

05:44.445 --> 05:46.812
I have whipped up
a five-course meal on my own

05:46.814 --> 05:49.047
Using a five-course meal
from boston market,

05:49.049 --> 05:53.185
Which I had delivered
from boston market on my own.

05:53.187 --> 05:54.419
[ sighs ] perfect.

05:54.421 --> 05:55.921
What if koontz walked by

05:55.923 --> 05:59.491
And saw an open flame
at a childrens hospital?

06:00.893 --> 06:02.828
[ sighs ]

06:03.663 --> 06:06.131
Oh, gentlemen,
what perfect timing.

06:06.133 --> 06:08.467
Please, be seated.

06:08.469 --> 06:10.736
Huh? How are you?

06:10.738 --> 06:12.237
Why aren't
the candles lit?

06:12.239 --> 06:13.872
What <i> aren't</i> the candles lit?

06:13.874 --> 06:16.174
Beth!

06:16.176 --> 06:19.478
Would you be so kind as to
light the candles, waiter beth?

06:19.480 --> 06:21.680
Thank you.

06:25.118 --> 06:27.919
Okay with the bowing.

06:45.104 --> 06:47.439
Thank you.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.575
Thank you!

06:50.577 --> 06:52.811
Where's chef phillipe?
We'd love to meet him.

06:54.580 --> 06:55.981
You want to meet
chef phillipe?

06:55.983 --> 06:57.416
He's right here.

06:57.418 --> 06:59.217
Please, one minute.

06:59.219 --> 07:00.218
<i>Un moment.</i>

07:00.220 --> 07:02.421
[ chuckles ]

07:04.190 --> 07:05.624
Hi, chef phillipe.

07:05.626 --> 07:07.659
Do you have a minute?

07:07.661 --> 07:10.429
[ french accent ]
oh, no! Are you crazy, sy?!

07:10.431 --> 07:12.330
[ normal voice ]
but these two young guys,

07:12.332 --> 07:13.799
They want to meet you.

07:13.801 --> 07:17.102
[ french accent ] I do not care!
They'll meet my cuisine!

07:18.438 --> 07:20.305
[ normal voice ]
did you hear that?

07:20.307 --> 07:22.007
Did you hear him?

07:22.009 --> 07:23.875
He said "do not"
instead of "don't."

07:23.877 --> 07:24.943
You know why?

07:24.945 --> 07:26.545
Because french people
are the only ones

07:26.547 --> 07:28.380
Who shun contractions
like that.

07:28.382 --> 07:30.348
You wanted to meet the chef.

07:30.350 --> 07:31.683
You heard the chef.

07:31.685 --> 07:33.718
He's in there.
Moving on.

07:33.720 --> 07:35.554
That didn't sound
like a real french accent.

07:35.556 --> 07:39.191
Trust me.
This food will sound french...

07:39.193 --> 07:40.659
To your mouths.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.127
<i>Bon app√©tit.</i>

07:42.129 --> 07:47.332
Gentlemen, please enjoy
typical french meatloaf

07:47.334 --> 07:48.967
With country gravy!

07:48.969 --> 07:50.035
With the bowing.

07:50.037 --> 07:53.104
Guess what, everyone?
I've got a thing!

07:53.106 --> 07:54.840
Sy, the fundraiser's running
an hour late!

07:54.842 --> 07:56.608
Where's koontz?
Where's koontz?

07:56.610 --> 07:57.709
Where is koontz?

07:57.711 --> 07:59.177
Koontz is, uh...
Koontz is coming.

07:59.179 --> 08:01.813
You did arrange his travel
from the airport, right?

08:01.815 --> 08:04.115
Ha! Me, arrange travel
like some kind of nurse?

08:04.117 --> 08:06.318
That's so funny I forgot --
[chuckles]

08:06.320 --> 08:07.786
I forgot to call koontz!

08:07.788 --> 08:09.221
Kip:
Sy, what's for dessert?

08:09.223 --> 08:10.455
What's for dessert?

08:10.457 --> 08:12.157
Ah, I guess
I'll have to call koontz.

08:12.159 --> 08:13.492
Go ahead. Call koontz.

08:13.494 --> 08:15.060
Beth, dessert!

08:16.028 --> 08:17.729
[ whimpers ]

08:19.298 --> 08:20.632
Here you go, boys.

08:20.634 --> 08:22.601
A milkshake with two straws

08:22.603 --> 08:24.369
So you can
"lady and the tramp" it up.

08:24.371 --> 08:25.370
Yum.

08:25.372 --> 08:26.638
Sy, why'd you take

08:26.640 --> 08:29.341
My glass
of extra-strength laxative?

08:29.343 --> 08:31.643
Hold it!

08:38.985 --> 08:40.051
Hey!

08:40.053 --> 08:42.821
I'm lactose dependent.
Live with it.

08:42.823 --> 08:44.155
I just got off the phone
with koontz.

08:44.157 --> 08:45.290
Lovely man.

08:45.292 --> 08:46.591
He'll be here
in 15 minutes,

08:46.593 --> 08:48.293
But all the donors
are about to leave.

08:48.295 --> 08:49.594
You have to keep them here.

08:49.596 --> 08:51.429
No!
<i>I'm</i> gonna keep them here!

08:51.431 --> 08:52.664
Can you imagine that?

08:52.666 --> 08:54.766
A nurse trying
to keep the donors here?

08:54.768 --> 08:58.937
Tell me everything that's
happened up to this point.

09:00.273 --> 09:01.540
Sy: No, no, no.

09:01.542 --> 09:03.008
Hey, everybody.
No, no, no. Please.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.977
Please, keep your seats,
and thank you for your patience.

09:05.979 --> 09:08.547
You've all -- you've all
come here to see koontz,

09:08.549 --> 09:10.315
And he's here.

09:10.317 --> 09:12.050
And you can see him.

09:12.052 --> 09:14.185
But he's...

09:14.187 --> 09:15.921
Behind that curtain.

09:15.923 --> 09:19.291
So...You'll see him in a --
in a minute.

09:19.293 --> 09:20.358
So, dean koontz --

09:20.360 --> 09:21.993
[ stomach rumbles ]

09:25.531 --> 09:26.831
[ rumbles ]

09:31.671 --> 09:33.572
[ gurgles ]

09:35.441 --> 09:37.208
I am so sorry.

09:37.210 --> 09:38.343
[ rumbles ]

09:38.345 --> 09:40.812
[ farts ]

09:49.589 --> 09:51.423
Thanks for coming.

09:51.425 --> 09:53.024
Thanks for coming.

09:53.026 --> 09:55.527
Want to rethink your donation?

09:55.529 --> 09:57.062
Thanks for serving.

09:57.064 --> 10:00.632
I just want to let you know
I just posted a terrible review.

10:00.634 --> 10:01.900
Can't wait to read it.

10:01.902 --> 10:04.569
And tell chef phillipe
we enjoyed the meal.

10:04.571 --> 10:07.138
He'll love knowing that.

10:13.913 --> 10:16.948
Excuse me.
My name is dean koontz.

10:16.950 --> 10:17.916
Yes, you are.

10:17.918 --> 10:20.285
Did I...
Miss the fundraiser?

10:20.287 --> 10:21.353
Yes, you did.

10:21.355 --> 10:23.054
Oh.
That's too bad.

10:23.056 --> 10:24.322
Yes, it is.

10:24.324 --> 10:26.191
Nice hospital.

10:30.262 --> 10:32.297
Now it's yours.

10:39.739 --> 10:42.073
Ah, there's koontz...

10:42.075 --> 10:43.675
With his keys...

10:43.677 --> 10:46.011
Doing his thing, huh?

10:46.013 --> 10:48.780
[ chuckles ]
classic koontz.

10:50.282 --> 10:52.183
I'm a really big fan.

10:54.453 --> 10:57.889
[ mid-tempo music plays ]
